Back Blurb

An exotic/erotic tale of murder, sex, revenge... and tender love!

A Japanese artist is abducted by the 108 Dragons, a Chinese crime syndicate, and forced to serve them as a master assassin! His codename: Crying Freeman---because he silently weeps each time he murders.

A beautiful, lonely young woman, a painted, witnesses a murder and knows the mysterious assassin will come for her next. She has never known love... until she meets her would-be killer, Crying Freeman! Unable to carry out his orders, Freeman Proceeds to tell her the bizarre story of how he was trained to kill again and again...

Created by two of Japan's best-known manga story-tellers, Kazuo Koike, author of LONE WOLF AND CUB, and Ryoichi Ikegami, artist of MAI, THE PSYCHIC GIRL, SANCTUARY, and SAMURAI CRUSADER.

description: The creeps are coming for you. They're lurking in the shadows, and they're near enough to touch. They used to be content to stay out of the glare of the city's bright lights. But bad things have been happening-bad things that only the creeps can see. And only the creeps can stop. The creeps are coming for you and they're whispering their names: Eyeball, Gurgle, Booger, Chitter, Breaker, Gelulite and Mrs. Skank. And though you may recoil from them in horror, (italic)they(italic) are not the monsters. And one day soon, your life may depend on them. CREEPS is coming for you from the minds of acclaimed Spectre and Martian Manhunter artist Tom Mandrake and Blue Devil co-creator and Shi writer Dan Mishkin. The Creeps are coming for you in a tale that mixes horror with heroism...and its own weird brand of humor. Their first adventure begins here. Give yourself the Creeps!

When you're nothing but a Creep, the world doesn't care if you live or die. And when Creeps of all shapes and sizes begin to disappear from the city's streets, there's no one who will lift a finger to help...except other Creeps. Creeps with special abilities. Creeps who know evil when they see it, and aren't afraid to call it by name. Homeless and on the run, their closest friends missing or murdered, the Creeps search out a truth so terrible that even they will be horrified by it. Because Genesys Corporation has a plan for the Creeps that takes horror to a new level. It's a plan fueled by corporate greed, which sometimes creates the scariest bogeymen of all. In this issue, you'll also meet Gurgle, the amphibian monstrosity who only wants to be loved, and Chitter, the man (or is he?) of a thousand bugs. Plus: a scene that may keep you out of the charity thrift store for good!

Amid the city's alleyways and darkened streets, someone is stalking the Creeps. And their only choice is to stalk back. But the unspeakably evil Genesys Corporation is well protected by power and politics, and the Creeps may be too late to rescue their missing friends. Though not too late to discover a horror even they are unprepared for - a horror that lurks deep within one twisted human heart!
